inn1.comm: length ball, just outside off, left alone. Charles concedes a bye
length ball, middle and leg, hits the leading edge and back to the bowler
short of a length, wide, left alone
five wides. Big wide down the leg side, and Charles has no chance
short of a length, on off, squares him up, takes the outside edge, which goes between the second slip and gully
length ball, on the pads, defended to midwicket
length ball outside off, left alone
wide length ball, left alone
another wide length ball, holds its line, left alone
short of a length, wide outside off, left alone. Falls well short of the keeper
holds its line outside off, beats Shehzad's push
another wide length ball, left alone
another leave outside off to seal a maiden
driven well to extra cover, past the man inside the circle
tailing back in a little, defended off the front foot
length ball outside off, left alone to angle away
short of a length, just outside off, defended
wide length ball, allowed to go through to the keeper
length ball outside off, left alone
another length ball outside off, left alone
short and wide, Shehzad gets his ball, gets on top of it, and cuts it past point for four

he has left it onto the stumps. Length ball outside off, he plants the front foot across, wants to the leave the ball alone, but he is late in doing so. The ball seams away a touch, hits the inside edge, and ricochets onto the stumps
wide length ball, gets a stride in, and leaves it alone
full, on off, pushed wide of cover for a single
nearly bowled him around the pads. Jamshes gets too far across to a full leg-side delivery, and is hit on the pad in front of the stumps. Pitching outside leg, though
length ball, angling in, defended to leg
angling in too far, but Roach is lucky that it takes a soft touch on the pad through to the keeper
half an appeal for lbw as this jags back in, but Hafeez seems to have got an inside edge
this one doesn't come in as much as expected, and beats the outside edge
another wide down the leg side. Roach' second
length ball, angling in, defended back to him
short of a length, outside off, dabbed to point
short of a length, nudged wide of point for one
wide length ball, holds its line, left alone
short of a length, outside off, no need to play at it again
wide length ball, holds its line, goes through to the keeper
length ball outside off, left alone again

Hafeez is bowled in the rain. What if they walk off now? Hafeez won't be a pleased man. The crowd has thrown away the umbrella and is enjoying this wicket. A bad leave. Doesn't cover his off stump, and Holder gets this length ball to jag back in and take the open invitation to hit the stumps
length ball outside off, left alone
on a length, on off, holds its line, worked to leg
full and straight, on off, dug out for a single
length ball outside off, angling away, allowed to go through to the keeper
down the wicket to drive this down the ground, but can't beat the diving Darren Bravo at mid-on
full outside off, defended to cover
short of a length, wide, left alone
full and straight, Misbah is in a bit of a tangle after moving across, but the bat comes down in time
short of a length, outside off, seams away, left alone
wide length ball, holds its line, left alone again
short and wide, cut away to third man for one

another leave and another wicket. This time it is lbw. Length ball, on off, or may be just outside, he is expecting to angle away, but it seams back in. Jamshed has made up his mind to leave it, and the ball hits him on the pad. Umpire Wilson takes his time before raising the finger. Hawkeye says it would have missed off stump. There is no DRS in this match. The controversial bit, though, is that WICB's media release on playing conditions stated: "DRS will have Hawkeye and Ultramotion"
short of a length, outside off, holds its line, beats the outside edge
full outside off, defended off the front foot
worked away into the leg side for two
short of a length, outside off, defended to cover
left alone outside off
short of a length, straight, defended back

what a superb catch by Charles. Golden duck for Shafiq. Holder on a hat-trick. Short of a length, on off, Shafiq plays the angle, the ball holds its line, squares him up, takes the edge. And Charles goes flying to his right towards first slip to pluck this one-handed
no hat-trick. Short of a length, outside off, left alone
wide length ball, another leave. This one is called a wide
but short. Length ball outside off, seams away slightly, takes the edge, but the soft hands make sure it falls short of the cordon
outswinger. Big. Length ball, angling in, seaming away, beats the outside edge. Top stuff from Holder
length ball, angling in, defended to leg
walks down the wicket to leave this one alone outside off
short of a length, on off, no room. Defended back to him
length ball outside off, defended from the crease
stays on a length, just outside off, defended from the crease again
slightly wider, swinging away, left alone
another leave outside off
short of a length, on off, defended from the crease. A maiden
wide down the leg side. Oh. Not given. He reckons Akmal has moved too far across, and this was missing leg by a few inches
length ball outside off, left alone
short of a length, just outside off, holds its line again, and beats him
walks down the wicket, defends this
falls short again. Akmal walks down again, but plays across the line, and gets a soft egde that falls short of slip
length ball, defended to cover
defended off the front foot
this one seams back in  from outside off, and beats Misbah's inside edge
short of a length, outside off, defended
short of a length, on off, defended from the crease
length ball outside off, left alone
short of a length, outside off, Charles does the rest
length ball outside off, holds its line, left alone
length ball outside off, another leave
short of a length, wide outside off, defended
soft outside edge again, and Pollard makes a diving save at gully
short of a length, outside off, defended off the front foot

huge shout for catch at the wicket, but not given. This is an unplayable delivery, but has Akmal actually played it? Short of a length, just outside off, you have to play the angle, but it seams away. West Indies are sure they have their man. Umpire Wilson thinks otherwise. No DRS, remember. Loud edge. Is the umpire cancelling out the previous decision? Umar Akmal didn't walk, but we won;t have these silly moral debates under my watch
length ball, defended
defended off the front foot
first run off the bat in 36 balls. Pushed wide of mid-on, and he takes a risky run. He would have been gone had the throw hit

Charles doesn't gather. Had he done so, this would have been a very tight call for stumping. Length ball holds its line, Akmal falls over, momentarily drags the foot out, but Charles hasn't collected it
driven nicely, leaning into the shot, pushed past cover. Finally off the mark. After 19 deliveries
whipped away. Akmal breaking free here. A length ball angling in, he moves a little across and hits it powerfully over square leg. First boundary since the fourth over
length ball outside off, defended off the front foot
defended off the back foot this time. Soft hands there
full, outside off, holds its line, beats the outside edge. Misbah not sure at all, and pushes away from its body
nearly there. He shimmies down to cover the movement, but fails to do so. This one seams away from a length, and beats the edge
short of a length, outside off, left alone agin
full outside off, he pushes at it, gets a thick edge along the ground to third slip. Fourth maiden for Holder
short of a length outside off, steered away to third man
drifting into the pads, worked away for an easy single
short of a length, takes it from middle and off and works to leg with the angle
short of a length, angling into the pads, clipped away fine of long leg where Holder makes a sliding save. No sponsor skirting on the boundary rope. That helps Holder
short of a length, on off, defended from the crease
full and straight, driven to mid-on
full, just outside off, pushed to mid-off
full again, just outside off, defended back to him
wide length ball, left alone this time
length ball outside off, Misbah defends off the front foot
wide length ball, he walks down and leaves alone
left alone outside off. Bravo begins with a maiden, seventh of the innings
on a length, angling in, defended off the front foot
full, angling in, driven to mid-on
length ball outside off, pushed past cover
short of a length, angling in, defended off the back foot
angling in, extra bounce, hits him on the thigh pad, goes for a leg bye
length ball, stops a touch, hits the high part of the defensive bat
walks down the wicket, takes a length ball, chips this over midwicket
walks down the wicket again, plays a pick-up shot to long leg
short of a length, hits Misbah on the pad as he walks down
short of a length, dabbed away to third man for one
length ball outside off, runs off the outside half of the bat for a single
short of a length, outside off, pushed to point

then there were five. Umar Akmal has been playing to leg a bit too often. This one - a length ball - stops a little on him, takes the leading edge, and Bravo takes a safe catch running back from mid-on
short of a length, seams back in alarmingly. Hits him high on the thigh pad
length ball outside off, runs off the inside half of the bat for a single
short of a length, just outside off, watchfully played out first up
full, into the pads, hit hard, but straight to mid-on
we have been expecting you, Mr Afridi. He starts off with a six here. Gets a nice little length ball in his swinging arc, and he lofts it over long-off. Some things ever change
short of a length, outside off, defended off the back foot
length ball, angling in, worked to leg for one
superb delivery. Short of a length, outside off, seams and kicks away. Beats him
short of a length, just outside off, defended to cover
short of a length, on off, Afridi can't do much more than defend
moves across the stumps to place this into the leg side for a single. He will keep the strike
short of a length, tucked away off the hip for one
short of a length, angling in, defended
on a length, on off, hits the high part of the defensive bat
heavy ball. Almost pitched on a length, but hits the top of the bat as Misbah defends
angling into the pads, pushed past midwicket for one
short of a length, outside off, defended off the back foot. Nearly squared up
wide length ball, left alone
bouncer, on the stumps, he ducks under it
defended off the back foot. Misbah wants to see Holder off
full outside off, steered away to third man for one
full toss, outside off, pushed past the diving mid-off for a couple
wide and full delivery, swinging away, beats the outside edge as Afridi looks for a drive
short of a length, outside off, played to the wide first slip
pushes at a wide one, guides it to third man for one
No. 2 for Afridi. He is going to swing hard if it is in his zone. This is a slower ball, on off and middle and cutting in, and he goes with that movement, and smashes it over long-on
full and wide, Afridi goes after this too, and goes over point for four

difficult chance dropped. Leading edges are always difficult at slip. Afridi looks to whip a length ball to leg, gets a healthy leading edge, high to the right of Gayle at the wide first slip. Gayle gets a hand to it, but can't hold on
dabbed away to third man for a single
and sharp turn first up. Although this goes too far down leg, and between the keeper and backward short leg. Misbah takes just the two. Keeping Afridi away from spin?
defended off the front foot
sharp offbreak again, but down the leg side again
tossed up outside off, defended off the front foot
nice shot. Misbah's first boundary, and would you believe it, it has come with a reverse sweep. Takes this from middle and leg, and places it between slip and point
offbreak, but too straight, worked around the corner for a single
watchfully defends a length-ball offbreak
flat, into the pads, paddled away to fine leg. Slip moving to leg even before the batsman has played his shot. The umpires need to watch out for that
length ball, on off, pushed to short midwicket
moves across and down the wicket, pushes a length ball to mid-off
short of a length, no room, defended back to him
defends a length ball back to him
moves across the stumps and down the wicket, but can't push this wide of Bravo

appeal for lbw as this one moves in and Misbah has moved too far across. From a length outside off this one jags back. The umpire says no. Inside edge? Or heading down leg? Neither an inside edge nor missing leg. Misbah has got away with one
carrom ball. Picks it well, places it past point for a single
short of a lenght, into the pads, worked away around the corner
flat, almost parallel six. Jumps down the wicket, gets to the pitch of the ball, doesn't let it turn, and sends it scurrying over mid-off
Afridi is on fire here. Narine pitches a little short, Afridi is waiting for it, backs away, and cuts it past point
short, but into the pads, tucked away for a single
short of a length, stays back to defend
short, too straight, Afridi lets it go down leg. Not called wide
bouncer this time, Afridi ducks under it
short of a length, outside off, Afridi goes for a big drive over mid-off. The bat is not even in the same ballpark as the ball
short of a length, sharp, middle and leg, going down. Afridi stays inside its line
slower ball, full, Afridi defends
bouncer, outside off, Afridi pulls all over it. Beaten on the bottom edge
offbreak, defended off the back foot
looks to reverse, is beaten down the leg side. Will be called a bye
turning down the leg side, this time it will be called wide
short of a length, punched down the ground for one
wide down the leg side again. Narine has lost his line a bit
pushed wide of midwicket for a single
carrom ball, defended off the front foot
short of a length, on off, Afridi backs away, makes room, and punches this point for four more. How the game is changing
length ball, middle and leg, gets a leading-edge, a strong one, to long-on
short of a length, outside off, moves across to defend
length ball outside off, stops at him, played uppishly past cover for one
short of a length, outside off, punched to point
full, middle and leg, but Misbah finds short midwicket
length ball, just outside off, defended from the crease
short of a length, played back to him
short again, but this turns sharply, and Afridi is cramped. Somehow, he places it wide of cover for one
wide down the leg side
another wide, this time Charles can't gather it either
full, flat, into the pads, pushed to square leg
some music went off at the PA system as Samuels let go another wide down the leg side. Sammy tries to get a dead-ball call, but fails
defended back to him
into the pads, nudged to square leg
paddled away from outside off for a single to fine leg
length ball, into the pads, worked away for a single
what an incredible shot. Plants the front foot down, gets under a length ball, and ramps it over - dragging it from outside off - over short fine leg
Welcome back Afridi. Fifty off 35. The whole game has turned. Gets a half-volley on off, and drills it over extra cover. Boom boom, looks like
short of a length, outside off, punched away between point and cover-point. It holds up near the boundary
full, middle and leg, driven to long-on for one
moves across to work this length ball into the leg side. Taken from in front of off
another wide down the leg side. Afridi has beaten West Indies off their rhythm
down the leg again, but not called wide because Afridi has moved too far across
short of a length, outside off, punched to cover
No. 4 for Afridi. Long hop from Samuels, he rocks back and pulls it over square leg. The wind carries it further
full, on off, driven to long-on
short of a length, outside off, punched to deep cover
short of a length outside off, Afridi wants to cut, but is beaten by extra bounce
short of length ball angling in towards the off stump, defended towards point
just outside off, Misbah shuffles across and tucks the ball towards short fine leg
huge lbw appeal, but no way that was out, way outside off when he is hit, all three stumps visible as he looks to play that
around off stump, Afridi again moves outside off and glides the ball towards fine leg
slanting down the leg side, that should have been a wide, but is not called perhaps because the batsman had moved across beyond the off stump
full ball is pushed back towards the bowler who, as is the norm, pretends to fire the ball back towards the stumps
first ball Afridi leans across and defends to the leg side
Afridi moves across from leg stump and slaps the ball towards cover
spinning in from a length, well outside off, defended by Misbah
goes for the reverse-sweep, he usually plays that stroke well, but this time it is off the toe of the bat, rolls towards the bowler
pushed towards mid-on for a single
six more, a full toss from Samuels, no way Afridi isn't going to swing at that, he does and connects superbly, sends the ball soaring over long-on to bring up the 100 stand
the wides count continues to mount, the West Indies coach will have plenty to say to his bowlers after this innings, this was down the leg side
slapped towards point off the back foot
fires this in, clipped behind square leg for a single
short of length ball outside off, 126.9kph, chopped towards point
seamed in after pitching well outside off, pulled towards midwicket for one more, a quiet over so far
full and fired into the pads, tucked towards square leg for a single, sorry that was off the pads for a leg-bye
full ball from round the wicket, pitching outside off, driven towards mid-off for one more
pitched up from over the wicket this time, tucked towards midwicket, think of a single and take it though the fielder is onto the ball quickly
full ball, looks to carve that through the off, edges it towards short fine instead
gets methodically forward and looks to tuck the ball past square leg, can't beat the fielder
pitched up and that is a wristy drive towards cow corner, Afridi gallops back for the second
short of length ball heading for the pads, clipped behind square leg for a single
short of a length, outside off, punched wide of point
slower short ball, beats Afridi's pull

no deep point, and to bowl a wide length ball. Not the smartest move. Afridi goes after it, and manages to play it over point. All three deep fielders on the leg side. What's more, the ball went into the wet cover
moves right across the stump to ram this to fine leg
full and straight, driven to long-on

finally West Indies get rid of Afridi, but has he done enough damage already? Slower ball, short of a length, outside off. Afridi doesn't pick it, and skies it towards deep midwicket where Sammy moves to his left to complete the catch. Flamboyant celebrations from both Sammy and Pollard
bouncer first up for Wahab. Hits him on the shoulder
short of a length, tucked away off the hip
slower ball, full, worked to leg for a single
full, angling in, played to short midwicket
short of a length, middle and leg, pushed back to him
dug in short, gets it to rise towards the chest, fended away
short of a length, tucked away into the leg side for one
short of a length, wide, but Riaz can't place it wide of point
fended away to leg for a single
short, wide, he rides the bounce, and nicely cuts it away in front of point for two
length ball, into the pads, defended to midwicket
this shortish ball holds its line outside off, and beats the outside edge
length ball, on off, defended to cover

goes wide of the crease, Riaz works it against the angle, towards third man. Riaz and Misbah go for the second. Darren Bravo throws at Misbah's end, but Pollard fails to collect and misses the run-out. Late to move back to the stumps
defended to leg
tucked away into the leg side for a single
moves across the line to get inside the line and work a length ball to long leg
wide of the crease, full outside off, defended back to him
length ball, into the pads, defended to leg
another length ball defended back to Roach
into the pads, nudged away for a single
nudged away around the corner
short of a length, outside off, dabbed away to point for one
pushed wide of extra cover for another single
slower ball from wide of the crease, defended from the crease
length ball, on off, defended with an open face
wide of the crease again, short of a length, and Riaz finds the man at point
just short. Riaz flicks across the line, finds midwicket on the half-volley
wide down the leg side. The first run off this over
slower ball, outside off, defended off the front foot
length ball, angling in, defended again. Just the wide from this over
backs away to try to hit, he follows him, hits the inside edge for a single
regulation pace short ball, Riaz goes to pull, gets a meaty top edge, finds fine leg. Quite a steepler
short of a length, pulled away to fine leg
short of a length, wide, defended to point
wide of the crease, tries the yorker, dug out to midwicket
length ball, outside off, defended with an open face
Misbah sells him a dummy. Backs away to make room, Bravo follows him, Misbah retreats. Wide called
full, on the pads, driven wide of long-on and "two" is the early call, and two they get
makes room again, Bravo follows him again with a slower ball. Misbah gets a single to leg
slower bouncer, cut away, Gayle misfields at point. Ajmal hands the strike over
full and straight, driven to long-on for one
length ball, on off, pushed to mid-off
short again, this time he has dabbed it between point and cover, comes back for the second
into the pads, nudged away softly, but they won't get a second here
angling into the pads, but Ajmal can't beat short midwicket
flicked away off the pads, Misbah back on strike
angling in towards middle and off, worked away quietly to bring up an important fifty. Gets a quiet applause from his gallery, and quietly acknowledges it
looks to pull, gets a bottom edge towards fine leg
pushed to mid-off. Misbah wants to steal a single, Bravo wants the run-out, Bravo takes his eye off the ball, fails to collect the ball, Misbah gets two
Ajmal wants to ram this, fails to make a connection, but this is a wide down the leg side
slower ball, mis-hit wide of square leg. Two available, but Misbah wants just the one. Okay, time has arrived. Misbah is going to open up now

Misbah is cross with himself. He had set this up for a final charge, but the moment he tries to hit, he has edged one. Well done by Bravo. Bowls a slower ball, Misbah is done in, and he edges it through to Charles
length ball, on off, early into the shot, ends up scooping it over cover. Good running too
slower ball, played to point, Ajmal wants one, but Asad sends him back
slower ball, goes between the bat and pad, and over the stumps
sees him back away, and slips in a quick and wide full ball. Beats him
down the wicket, ducks into a bouncer, and the periscope gets a him a single to third man
slower ball, short, beats his cut
slogs at one, and gets a lucky edge over the keeper's head for four
down the wicket to play this slower ball to deep midwicket for one
short, slow, dabbed away to cover-point
Pollard's towel came off as he let go off the ball but Ajmal goes ahead with his attempt to ramp it. The slower ball doesn't arrive at all, and somehow he toe-ends into the safe zone around mid-on
slower ball, clipped over short midwicket
makes room to loft this half-volley over the bowler's head for a couple
short of a length, angling away, smashed back, but can't beat Bravo
what a timely six. Asad Ali charges at him, gets a slower ball in his zone, and swings hard at it, clearing midwicket with ease
fast yorker. Finally. Brother, where were thou? Squeezes under the bat, and hits the outside of the off stump
and Irfan smacks a four. Gets a low full toss, hits it hard, somehow connects it well, and the mid-off is up. Beats the man to his right

inn2.comm: full, into the pads, sneaks a leg-bye

full toss at the base of off. Charles has missed it. What a first ball to get. A near yorker from that height at 146ks. Before Charles can say hello, the off stump is uprooted. Irfan is running in circles in celebration
full outside off, swinging away. Left alone
this one angles in, defended from the crease
short of a length, just outside off, defended off the back foot
short of a length, outside off, left alone
clipped away off the pad to get off the mark
length ball, swinging in, defended in front of middle and leg
full and swinging in, pushed to mid-off
more swing, defended in front of his body
makes this one go away with the angle. Bravo is looking for the movement back in, and is beaten
length ball outside off, left alone
yorker again. Irfan is on today. Kept out well by Gayle
full, just outside off, dug out to cover
hit him just above the thigh pad. Short of a length, quick, extra bounce. That has stung. Gayle rubs his groin, the Pakistan fielders getting chirpier and chirpier
and hits the thigh pad this time. Stays short of a length, and beats him for pace again
stays short of a length, into the ribs this time. Gayle has to defend
goes fuller, aimed at top of off, Gayle has to be alert to keep this out. Irfan yet to be scored off
flashes at a length ball that is seaming away from him. Beaten
fuller, on off, defended off the back foot
full, swinging towards off, defended back to him
short of a length, stays low, angles away, beats the toe end of the bat
half-volley, driven, but finds mid-off
first run off the bat in the last 17 deliveries. Short of a length, angling across, Bravo punches, gets a thick edge past second slip
short of a length, outside off, defended to point
first runs off Irfan. They came off an edge. Bravo goes to cut, gets this to go off the toe end and past the second slip

Bravo is, like the man he tries to emulate, walking. Extra bounce again. Short of a length, rising into the ribs, Bravo wants to get inside the line and work it away, but is strangled down the leg side, and gloves it through

huge lbw shout. This is full so there is every chance this has pitched within the stumps. Samuels is caught on the back foot and dead in front, the only question is, did it pitch outside leg? Reifell thinks outside, so he says not out. Replays say it pitched just outside leg
pushed through just outside off, at 145ks, and beats the outside edge

Gayle can't run. Not sure why he tried this single when he knows he can't run fast anymore. Samuels pushes it towards cover, and is anxious to get off the mark. Gayle hesitates before going, but even if he had set off immediately he couldn't have beaten Misbah's direct hit at his pace
accurate, on a length, headed for off, defended off the back foot
short of a length, outside off, left alone
wide half-volley, Samuels pushes at it. Gets no timing whatsoever
short of a length, just outside off, defended off the back foot
full and wide, Samuels gets some timing going, but pushes this straight to point
gets some movement in, runs off the thick outside edge, past then third slip, for a single
short of a length, angling away, chest-high collection for Akmal
length ball outside off, 147ks, left alone
extra bounce again. That must have stung as the ball hit the handle of the bat. From short of a length it rose, and Samuels was in discomfort
short of a length, angling away, and extra bounce again. Beaten
short of a length, pitched outside leg, dropped to leg for one
full and fast, just outside off, defended with an open face
short of a length, on off, defended
full, nearly a yorker, dug out back to him
short of a length, angling towards top of off. Defended from the crease
short of a length, outside off, steered away to third man
length ball outside off, holds its line after pitching, left alone
short of a length, angling in, worked away for one
short of a length, outside off, gets good bounce. Left alone
slightly fuller, allowed to angle across his body
on a length, on off, defended off the high part of the bat

slightly short of a length, but gets it to rise towards the chest. Simmons has both feet in the air, still struggles to control it. His head falls back instinctively in self defence. Somehow it stays low
length ball, but still hits the high part of the defensive bat
wide down the leg side
short of a length, just outside off, left alone
driven on the up, nicely, but Asad gets a hand to it in the follow-through
length ball outside off, defended with an open face
half-volley, Samuels finally finds some fluency. Drives this between the bowler and mid-off
another half-volley. This is swinging in, but he manges to get the front leg out of the way and drives this wide of mid-on for four
this is short of being a half-volley, and Samuels can't reach the drive. it swings back in to beat the inside edge
short of a length, on off, defended off the back foot
heavy ball first up. The gun might say only 136ks, but it is accurate and hits him high on the bat
full outside off, Simmons goes for the drive, and is beaten by the angle
edged but short of slip. Slightly short of a length, angling away, Simmons is a bit squared up but plays with soft hands
length ball outside off, left alone
superb fielding from Shehzad. Makes a diving stop at point and even when on the ground he lets rip a throw at the only stump visible. Simmons is just about back
full, fast, outside off, and beats the edge
starts off with a quick offbreak. Defended off the back foot
another quick offbreak, beats the inside edge, hits the pad, but it headed down leg
stays quick, full and straight. Defended off the back foot
another quick offbreak, but this gives him a bit of room. Pushed wide of cover for one
offbreak, turning in towards off. Defended
the doosra. Squares him up, takes the edge, but dies to the right of first slip
length ball outside off, left alone
length ball, on off, hits the high part of the bat
short of a length, pitched outside off, he can go back and nudge it away for one
slight swing back in, but not much. Samuels ends up playing inside the line of it. Beaten
Shehzad makes another full-length diving save at point top save runs
short of a lenght, on the pads, worked away for a single
short of a length, goes back to push this back to Ajmal
quick offbreak, 90ks, Samuels does well to get the bat down in time and works it to leg
big shout for lbw as Simmons tries to cut Ajmal and is beaten comprehensively. Hits the pad in front of leg, and would have gone down leg
flighted on middle and off, defended off the front foot
full, middle and of,f driven to short cover
another failed attempt at a cut. Simmons is not picking the right length, and Ajmal is not bowling short. The outside edge is beaten
length ball outside off, left alone
slightly short of a length, just outside off, watches it into the keeper's gloves
wide length ball, left alone again
draws the drive away from the body. Riaz has been pretty quick. Beats him with the pace and the angle
back to disciplined leaves outside off
full outside off, driven to deep cover for one
tossed up outside off, defended off the front foot
goes back to a length ball, the ball stays a touch low. Samuels manages to keep it out
the doosra. Samuels goes back again, and is beaten by the away movement
bat-pad, but it goes straight of short leg. Something happening every ball
slides this down the leg side
quick offbreak, again stays low, Simmons is back again. That nearly squeezes under it
flighted for a change, worked away off the pad for one
short of a length, on off, dabbed away to third man for one
wide half-volley, driven, but there is a deep cover in place
steered away to third man
bouncer, middle and leg, ducks under it
drops and runs. A good call this time. They make it before Shehzad can swoop in
length ball outside off, left alone
flighted on off, defended off the back foot
flat offbreak, Samuels stays back in defence
slightly short of a length, Samuels jumps back, and is cramped by the turn
full, on off, defended back to him
flat, into the pads, worked away for a single
quick toppie, he is back again, and has to keep a low-bouncing delivery out
short of a length, just outside off, defended off the back foot
shapes up to swing back in, but seams away after pitching. Beats the outside edge
short of a length, stays a touch low, kept out off the back foot
length ball outside off, Samuels defends from the crease
short of a length, angling away,opens the face on it, takes a single to third man
short of a length, middle and off, played with an open face
short of a length, turning in towards off, defended off the back foot
flat, outside off, cut away to third man
dabbed away to point
full and fast, defended back to him
goes back to a length ball, places it wide of cover for one
full, on off, defended to cover
quick legbreak, defended off the front foot
full, middle and leg, driven to long-on
this one doesn't turn, takes the inside edge onto the pad, and goes for a sharp single into the leg side
flighted legbreak, defended off the front foot
some drift and turn, smothered after a good stride in
slightly short this legbreak is, cut away to deep point for one
stays back to play an offbreak back to Hafeez
stays slightly low, Simmons defends off the back foot
fuller, slightly higher, blocked off the front foot
some drift into the pads, clipped away to short midwicket
flatter, quicker, hits his pad after beating the inside edge
short of a length, turning into the pads, pushed to long-on to break the maiden

Has Simmons dragged the back foot? Lovely delivery. A quick legbreak that dips on him, drawing him forward and then spinning past the edge. Akmal is quick with the stumping. Simmons has dragged his foot onto the crease. I don't see any part of the toe behind the line, but it is up to the third umpire on how he interprets the pictures. He agrees with me. Given

and with one come two for Afridi. Absolutely sensational comeback by Afridi. No. 350 too. Afridi knows Bravo might be mindful of the legbreak that he had bowled previously, and slips in the quicker slider to catch him dead in front. The Boris-Becker celebration is back. How good to see it back
this is a quick legbreak, headed towards off, goes off the outside half for a single. Nearly there then
flighted on middle and off, defended to cover
huge lbw shout as the slider beats the inside edge. That's a really really close shout. Not given. Possibly sliding down leg. Replays show it wasn't. It was pretty adjacent
short of a length, quick pushed to cover
slides this down leg. Called wide
defended off the back foot
sharp turn, down the leg side
full and straight, pushed back to him
full, on off, played back to him
driven to long-off for one
down the wicket, drives to mid-off, takes a single
drifting down, clipped away fine, Irfan makes a diving save at short fine leg
flat outside off, can't beat point with the back cut
flighted this time, pushed past cover for a single
legbreak, on off, defended with an open face
another legbreak. And some dip. Pollard is pushing in front of the body, and is beaten
full and outside off, pushed back to Afridi, who lets a throw rip at the keeper. Pollard plays a mock shot to the throw too
down the wicket, beaten in flight, pushes this to midwicket
appeal for catch at the wicket, down the leg side, but that's mostly to avoid the wide call. And they succeed
driven down to long-on for one
flat offbreak, nudged around the corner to bring up the 50. No sarcastic applause from the crowd
down the wicket, punched on the up, but straight to mid-off
flat, into the pads, defended

Afridi juts his chest out again, and his team-mates surround him again. Pollard's horror home season continues. Drills a legbreak straight down long-off's throat. West Indies' two captains this season have failed yet again. And they removed Sammy
that's a 102kph legbreak. How do you play it? You don't. You get beaten
full, on off, quick, played back to him
length ball, into the pads, defended to leg
slower this time, dipping drifting legbreak, beats the outside edge
angling in, nudged to leg to break the maiden
flat offbreak, defended off the front foot
quick offbreak again, stays back to defend
leaves an offbreak outside off, and it nearly shaves the off bail
turning into the pads, defended
defended with an open face
short of a length, no room, pushed back. Another maiden
short of a length, defended back to him

appeal for pad first, Reifell says pad first. Quick legbreak again, pitches middle and leg, straightens,is headed towards off, hits the pad first, and has been rightly given out lbw. Afridi raises his arms in elation again. Lala in line for five
this is a front-of-the-hand seam-up delivery Roach is clearly late, but this is sliding down leg. Afridi realises it midway into the appeal . They get two leg-byes
flighted on off, defended off the front foot
quicker legbreak, blocks off the front foot
slower, higher, wider, Roach tries to drive, finds short cover
length-ball offbreak, defended off the front foot
another front-foot defensive
pushed wide of cover for a single
flighted, goes of the inside half of the bat for a single
bat-pad, but doesn't carry to the diving short leg. Nasir might have got up a touch too soon
stays a touch low, defended
legbreak, dipping, breaking, beats him
tossed up, middle and leg, defended back to him
short of a length, breaks away, beats the cut

easy does it. That's five for Afridi. Where were you, Shahid? We have missed you. Tosses this up in the air, slower too, gets a leading edge from Roach, which comes back at him for a comfortable catch. That's the third time Afridi has taken five and scored a fifty in the same match. No one else has ever done it even twice
short of a length, on off, defended
fuller, legbreak, Narine defends off the back foot
full, middle and leg, driven hard over mid-off for four. The previous boundary came in the 10th over
pushed around off, defended from the crease
sharp offbreak, hits the pad
short of a length, defended from the crease
defended off the front foot
fired into the pads, keeps Sammy at that end
quick legbreak, defended from the crease
length ball legbreak, defended from the crease again
full, outside off, defended back to him
slower through the air, gets some turn, hits the inside half of the bat
offbreak, short of a length, played with an open face
another maiden from Afridi as Narine defends off the back foot. Look at those figures: 7-2-6-5
turning down the leg side, they will take a leg-bye
tossed up outside off, left alone
short of a length, outside off, pushed back to him
length-ball offbreak, pushed past cover
short of a length, pushed to point
defended off the front foot
another leg-before appeal. Narine is caught on the back foot, but it is turning too much
sharp legbreak. Slightly short, Narine goes for the cut, hits the bottom edge
full and fast, dug out
legbreak, turning too far down leg. Called a wide
short of a length, into the pads, pushed away for a single
what a superb legbreak. Dipping on him, drifting in, then leaving him after pitching. Beaten comprehensively
pushed wide of long-off for a couple. What a poor over by Afridi's standards today
fired down the leg side, concedes a wide
sharp offbreak, hits him high on the pad
flat, into the pads, worked away for a single
heaved away past midwicket
plays the pick-up shot off the toes, over wide long-on, gets a four. A monumental occasion: the run rate crosses two an over
driven into the covers
huge shout for lbw as Ajmals fires one in, but an inside edge has saved Narine
yorker, just outside off, dug out back to him
slower bouncer, Sammy has no clue about it. Somehow gets under it. He is on his backside. Called wide foe height anyway. With that, West Indies cross Afridi's score
quicker bouncer, and the ball arrives even before he is ready for the pull. Goes to extra cover for one
short, and a big wide down the leg side
slightly short of the yorker, and he drives hard at it, and past cover
short ball, he sees it early, and pulls it over mid-on
slower length break, runs off the outside half of the bat for one
length ball, angling in, defended off the back foot
defends an offbreak off the front foot
tospinner, goes off the outside half of the bat and past slip
goes back to a length ball, and nearly chops it one
slower through the air, higher flight too, beats the inside edge with the offbreak
short of a length, punched to the left of cover where Shafiq makes a diving save
angled into the pads, lobs to short leg
pulled away to wide long-on for one
misfires this yorker, concedes a leg-bye
top-edges a pull and it clears Asad Ali who is running back from short fine leg
full toss, on off, pushed to cover
slower ball, full, nicely defended to cover
short of a length, rising towards the chest, nicely rises up with it and defends
how did that miss? Sammy swings and misses by a mile, but the offbreak turns down the leg side
full, on off, driven to cover
slightly shorter, defended off the back foot
slogged away, and for some reason deep midwicket is well inside the boundary. He is lobbed. It was a sitter for Shafiq had he been on the rope
tries the big drive, gets an inside edge
angled in, no turn, Narine goes back to punch it to point
short of a length, outside off, punched to deep cover
legbreak, but too far down leg. Another wide

No. 6 for Afridi. Where was he hiding all this while? Short of a length, outside off, stops at him a touch, lobbed to short cover. This is Afridi's personal best, and the best figures by anybody in West Indies
the quick seam-up delivery, hits the inside edge
is that the googly? Definitely goes in. Defended off the back foot
quick legbreak, Holder defends off the front foot

it's all over. Afridi has seven. One of the all-time great performances in an ODI. Holder is playing for the legbreak, but this is the slider, and he is caught in front of off and on the back foot. No need to even appeal for this. West Indies' lowest total against Pakistan, and their worst score against any team at home. These are the second-biggest figures ever in an ODI. And a fifty to go with it
